Customising Inserts using entity context
A common customization pattern is that you want to store additional information on the
application database whenever a Cúram entity is inserted. In "classic" Cúram you might have
extended the out-of-the-box entity but this is discouraged for code constructed using Persistence
Infrastructure because of the undesirable dependencies it creates between custom code and out-
of-the-box code. Instead, you'll create a whole separate entity that gets updated in synch with the
original.
Let's take a typical use case. A method of a façade class is called by the Cúram client to insert
data collected on a UIM page. The façade method gets data from its parameters, and invokes
service layer APIs to create a new entity instance and persist it. You want to collect additional
information and persist it on a new entity along with the original, using the same primary key
value.
The initial steps you will take are as follows, and are the same as described for "classic" Cúram
code in the Cúram Server Developer's Guide:
