In summary, what we've done is to provide a listener which receives insert events for one entity
and performs inserts on another, supplemental entity. The data for the supplemental entity was
piggybacked on "entity context", and will normally have been provided via a façade. However,
it's important to note that this listener pattern works no matter where the insert was invoked from,
although you'll find you have to decide how to handle the situation where an insert was performed
