Add state transition validation logic
The CodetableState and Transition helper classes provide the following standard validation to
disallow any transition which is not explicitly specified. For example, the state transition diagram
does not permit an entity instance in the closed state to transition to any other state; by default,
any attempts to.suspend() an entity instance which is currently closed will result in this error
being raised: Cannot transition from 'Closed' to 'Suspended'.
You can add logic (typically to perform validations and/or notifications) to the following places:
•
in your State objects:
•
onEnter - this method is called whenever a transition occurs which attempts to enter this
State;
